        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Lizalfos</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> The largest factors I have noticed in fearing have been level and Magic Resist.</P><P>Went in to Rathe Arena and dropped CHA dow to about 15, I think.  Cast fear on a even conning friend for an hour straight (easily 100 fears, I waited for it to wear off and her to come back before refearing).  25 resists.  Average duration was 5 min on invoke fear.</P><P>Maxed out my cha as high as I could, 100 (nobles robe &lt;I know, I gave my blackened crystalline to my GF's chanter&gt;, 25 cha stien, ditching my nettled kelp and my sorcerous bowl) and had a shammy friend join me for a cha buff.  Feared again for an hour.  Extremely similar results.  26 Resists, average duration on fear being again about 5 min.  Got bored of my experiment and went to bed.</P><P>Next day, I got the same friends back in rathe arena and we finished it.  This time, I had the feared take off all Magic Resist gear, dropping her down to 30 MR I think.  Dropped my cha down again and feared for an hour.  3 resists.  Average duration being 5 min again.</P><P>Raised my cha back to 100, and refeared for another hour.  4 resists and about the same duration as before.</P><P>All I can say on this is duration seems to be mostly random, as I had some fears lasting as long as 7 or 8 min, and some going out in 30 secs.  I would guess level comes in to play there.  She was an even con.  I think what I did shows MR is the main factor in does the fear land or is resisted.  CHA may play some effect in all this, but not a very noticable one.  Perhaps it is a secondary in the duration, but after fearing for 4 hours total, I could not really tell what the difference really was.</P><P>CHA does indeed help you landing your undead charms, possibly Screaming Terror, but I haven't been bored anough to test ST.  However, I have only used my undead charms when raiding Lguk or ToFS *only on the wedding floor* and my pet died during a fight with 2 or more creatures.  It has limited uses I have found thus far, and really is only good for dealing with a place you have 2 mobs together and you can't single pull them.  Otherwise, I would say it is largely a line of spells I have not really used, but I'm sure there are some inventive uses for them out there.  Otherwise, it's also fun for scaring noobs in Oasis or breaking the spawn, but kill your spec cause once the spawn is broken, he will be much better.</P><P>edit: the neg 25 cha mask is for an iksar necro quest for the 3rd or 4th skullcap.  Iksar only, but is a pretty lame cap.  just get a nightshade wreath.</P><P><BR>Death takes on many faces, yours takes on mine.<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916" target="_blank">Lizalfos Deathscale</a><BR><a href="http://www.guildportal.com/Guild.asp?GuildID=1637&TabID=594" target="_blank">Blood Red Rose</a></P><P>Edited by - Lizalfos on 08/02/2002  10:08:16</font></td>
